{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/3206","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/3206/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/3206/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/3206/events","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/3206","id":13847494,"number":3206,"title":"image viewer should use exif data to rotate image before displaying","user":{"login":"gjanssens","id":619393,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/4a802bf984fbfdb7026d5854bd2fd3b5?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f67aad2b5e8bb724f4830aa13f6b243c2.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"4a802bf984fbfdb7026d5854bd2fd3b5","url":"https://api.github.com/users/gjanssens","html_url":"https://github.com/gjanssens","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gjanssens/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gjanssens/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gjanssens/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gjanssens/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gjanssens/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gjanssens/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gjanssens/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gjanssens/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gjanssens/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","assignee":null,"milestone":null,"comments":4,"created_at":"2013-05-01t13:00:22z","updated_at":"2013-05-01t18:39:20z","closed_at":"2013-05-01t16:26:48z","pull_request":{"html_url":null,"diff_url":null,"patch_url":null},"body":"many camera's these days use exif metadata to define whether an image was taken in landscape or portrait mode, yet always store the image in landscape mode.\r\n\r\nto properly display such images, the exif data should be parsed for rotation information and then apply the proper rotation before displaying.\r\n\r\ni have found that both the image viewer in the webinterface (tested with owncloud 4.5 only) and the most recent owncloud client on android ignore the exif rotation information. as a result, images are displayed in the wrong direction. turning the android device to put the image upright triggers the auto-rotate function resulting in the image being rotated back to its wrong orientation.","closed_by":{"login":"kondou-ger","id":1410802,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/917dab919ae812f8252b2f501c514b19?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2fd07869ed62cb1b7f88b731956ab913ee.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"917dab919ae812f8252b2f501c514b19","url":"https://api.github.com/users/kondou-ger","html_url":"https://github.com/kondou-ger","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kondou-ger/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kondou-ger/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kondou-ger/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kondou-ger/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kondou-ger/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kondou-ger/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kondou-ger/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kondou-ger/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kondou-ger/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false}}